{{GeoGroup|article=Operation Sculpin}}

The '''United States's Sculpin nuclear test series'''<ref name=LT_1 /> was a group of 7 [[nuclear test]]s conducted in 1990-1991. These tests <ref group=note>A bomb test may be a salvo test, defined as two or more explosions "where a period of time between successive individual explosions does not exceed 5 seconds and where the burial points of all explosive devices can be connected by segments of straight lines, each of them connecting two burial points and does not exceed 40 kilometers in length". {{cite paper|first=V. N., Editor in Chief|last=Mikhailov|title=Catalog of World Wide Nuclear Testing|publisher=Begell-Atom, LLC|url=http://www.iss-atom.ru/ksenia/catal_nt/1.htm}}</ref> followed the ''[[Operation Aqueduct]]'' series and preceded the ''[[Operation Julin]]'' series.

{{see also|List of nuclear weapons tests of the United States}}

